<subSubSection id="41A8AC71F81602A2FC564C8904DC38A7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="20D22AD235868E80486FE334A2F3C8C4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="754C9A5BA98E3C9E68045F7C87A7A89D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Endemic to Peru (Ancash, Ayacucho, Huancavelica, 
<normalizedToken id="654738D9ED25AD5F34032B1C3D08511B" originalValue="Huánuco">Huanuco</normalizedToken>
[expected], 
<normalizedToken id="C242055975DEFB07450D69EC9515D6E7" originalValue="Junín">Junin</normalizedToken>
, Lima). It grows in rocky outcrops, scree slopes, and on cryoturbated soils of the subhumid and humid puna ecoregions, between elevations of 3850-5000 m (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6B642DB66A359739329CA984960A6B4E" captionStart="Figure 24" captionStartId="F24" captionText="Figure 24. Distribution map of Xenophyllum decorum (left hand, closed triangle), X. amblydactylum (left hand, open circle), and X. dactylophyllum (right hand)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.158.50848.figure24" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448904" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">24</figureCitation>
